  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Motivational interviewing (MI) has been shown to be an effective strategy in targeting
      obesity in adolescents and parental involvement has been associated with increased
      effectiveness. The aim of the study is to evaluate and compare the role of parental
      involvement in MI interventions for obese adolescents
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
